In Section 2, the need for a network analysis approach to fully capture the complex, multi-level interactions between indicators in the SDG network is emphasised. After removing insignificant relationships, we conduct a network analysis on the SDGs network consisting of 108 nodes and 3,012 interactions. The full descriptions of indicators are provided in supplementary material (Table S3). Centrality analysis provided a list of highly connected, eigen-central, bridging, and focal indicators (Table 2
                           ), which are visualised in Fig. 8
                           . Reviewing Table 2, we observe that the top indicators remain consistent across all three centrality measures, except for indicator 16.1.1.b. While this particular indicator is highly connected, it is not amongst the top eigen-central or focal indicators.
